{
  "doc_id": "34022",
  "text": "In high-risk neutropenic patients, especially in relation to stem cell transplantation or anti-leukemia therapy, patients are generally hospitalized and treatment is still consisting of broad spectrum intravenous antibiotics [CITATION_1] . Best approach for these patients is based on local protocols, which take local microbial resistance data into account. These protocols are beyond the scope of this overview.",
